text: Lilly Singh (born 26 September 1988) is a Canadian YouTuber, vlogger, comedian, television host, writer and actress. She is mostly known by her YouTube former username IISuperwomanII. ==Career== She began her YouTube channel in October 2010. She has gotten over 3 billion total views on YouTube and over 15 million subscribers. She has a second channel, titled "Lilly Singh Vlogs". In 2016, she was said to be the third most paid YouTuber at $7.5 million. In 2016, she got her first movie. It was called A Trip to Unicorn Island. In 2017, she published her first book. It was called How to Be a Bawse: A Guide to Conquering Life. In March 2019, it was announced that she would host her own NBC late-night talk show. It is called A Little Late with Lilly Singh. == Personal life == In February 2019, Singh came out as bisexual. ==References== ==Other websites== * * Lilly Singh channel website Category:LGBT comedians Category:Comedians from Toronto Category:1988 births Category:Living people Category:American television talk show hosts Category:York University alumni Category:LGBT actors Category:Canadian YouTubers Category:Actors from Toronto Category:Canadian bloggers Category:Canadian voice actors Category:Canadian movie actors Category:Canadian television actors Category:Canadian LGBT writers
